ically, for Jankelevitch, evil is both the impetus and the obstacle to forgiveness.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mrz 2022) 0aForgiveness. 4aJewish Studies. 4aPhilosophy & Theory. 7aPHILOSOPHY / General.2bisacsh  aMemory.  aRepentance.  aResentment.  aUnderstanding.  aethics.  aevil.  aforgiveness.  aphenomenology.  areligion.  atemporality.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertFordham University Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015z978311072903040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780823262984zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780823262984423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780823262984/original  a978-3-11-072903-0  Fordham University Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK